{"id":"226205967_On_the_purity_of_limiting_Gibbs_state_for_the_Ising_model_on_the_Bethe_lattice","abstract":"We give a proof that for the Ising model on the Bethe lattice, the limiting Gibbs state with zero effective field (disordered state) persists to be pure for temperature below the ferromagnetic critical temperatureT\nc\nF\nuntil the critical temperatureT\nc\nSG\nof the corresponding spin-glass model. This new proof revises the one proposed earlier.","authors":["Pavel Bleher","J. Ruiz","Valentin A. Zagrebnov"],"meta":["April 1995Journal of Statistical Physics 79(1):473-482","DOI:10.1007/BF02179399"],"references":["38330654_Extremity_of_the_disordered_phase_in_the_Ising_model_on_the_Bethe_lattice","305979431_A_branching_process_showing_a_phase_transition","266465936_Remarks_on_the_Limiting_GIbbs_States_on_a_Jl-Tree","265333396_Gibbs_Measures_and_Phase_TransitionsBerlin_Walter_de_Gruyter","264956012_On_Pure_Phases_of_the_Ising_Model_on_the_Bethe_Lattices","239744606_A_Branching_Process_Showing_a_Phase_Transition","235522165_Random-field_Ising_model_on_a_Bethe_lattice","231024226_Critical_Behavior_of_the_Bethe_Lattice_Spin_Glass","38386396_Remarks_on_the_limiting_Gibbs_states_on_a_d_1-tree"]}